The paper deals with the problem of crossing minimization in graph drawing, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem is also related to graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). The paper presents hardness results and approximation algorithms, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and algorithm design and analysis (cs.SI).
